JOHANNESBURG – South Africa’s headline consumer inflation remained steady at 4.5% year-on-year in June, unchanged from the May figure, data from Statistics South Africa showed on Wednesday. On a month-on-month basis prices inched up 0.4% from a 0.3% increase previously. Core inflation – which excludes the prices of food, non-alcoholic beverages, petrol and energy – was at 4.3% year on year versus a 4.1% increase in May, and was at 0.4% month on month compared to a rate of 0.0% last month. (Reuters) 